  "prompt": "Where did pizza originate?",
  "response": "Pizza, as we know it today, originated in **Naples, Italy**, in the 18th and 19th centuries. The dish evolved from flatbreads topped with oils, herbs, and other ingredients, which were common in ancient Mediterranean cultures. However, the modern pizza\u2014featuring tomatoes, mozzarella cheese, and basil (the classic \"Margherita\")\u2014was popularized in Naples.\n\nThe story goes that in 1889, Neapolitan pizzaiolo (pizza maker) Raffaele Esposito created the \"Pizza Margherita\" to honor Queen Margherita of Savoy. He used tomatoes (red), mozzarella (white), and basil (green) to represent the colors of the Italian flag, and it became an iconic dish.\n\nWhile Naples is credited with the creation of pizza, earlier forms of flatbreads with toppings date back to ancient civilizations like the Egyptians, Greeks, and Romans.",
